<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>HTML Hyperlinks Demonstration</title>
</head>
<body>
    <p>Hyperlinks in HTML are created using the <a> tag with the href attribute to specify the link
        destination. The target attribute determines how the link is opened.</p>
        <h1>Basic Hyperlink</h1>
        <a href="https://google.com">Visit google.com!</a>
        <h1>Open Link in a New Tab</h1>
        <a href="https://www.wikipedia.org/" target="_blank">Visit Wikipedia.com!</a>
        <h1>Open Link in Parent Frame</h1>
        <a href="https://www.example.com/" target="_parent">Visit W3Schools!</a>
        <h1>Open Link in Full Window</h1>
        <a href="https://www.bbc.com/" target="_top">Visit W3Schools!</a>
</body>
</html>
